div.div:
Idea for more generic missing block detection:
* send M = 0..31, S = 0, B = 0..31
* get status
status: S = 0, ---x--x-------------------------
* send M = 0..31, S = 1, B = 3, 5, 32..61
* get status
staus: S = 1, x-------------------------------
* send M = 0..31, S = 0, B = 3, 62..92
* get status
staus: S = 1, x-------------------------------==> Invalid S bit, so all packets lost
...
Pros:
* more generic approach
* less packets needed in case of missing blocks
* no need for "bank" concept
Cons:
* maybe a little more complicated code
* one more byte in the packet
